The paper deals with list decoding of random linear codes and the use of the Restricted Isometry Property (RIP) for this purpose. This connects to several areas of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), machine learning (cs.LG), and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of RIP in compressed sensing and the analysis of Gaussian processes also suggest a connection to these areas.
